blank%5C%22%3Estereotypes%20of%20DINKs%3C%2Fa%3E%20growing%20old%20alone%2C%20many%20are%20using%20their%2030s%20to%20forge%20the%20deepest%20connections%20of%20their%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20from%20becoming%20aunties%20to%20their%20friends'%20children%20to%20forming%20relationships%20in%20the%20unlikeliest%20of%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22428e05e6-6785-4202-b931-a41bb1946941%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMillennial%20DINKs%20might%20not%20know%20where%20they%20fit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20households%20have%20changed%20dramatically%20since%20boomers%20were%20parents.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusafacts.org%2Farticles%2Fhow-has-the-structure-of-american-households-changed-over-time%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%201960%2C%20married%20parents%20made%20up%2044%25%20of%20all%20US%20households%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%202022%2C%20they%20were%20outnumbered%20by%20both%20single%20people%20and%20child-free%20couples%20%E2%80%94%20that%20year%2C%20there%20were%2038.1%20million%20married%20and%20childless%20households%2C%20a%20140%25%20increase%20over%201960%2C%20according%20to%20USA%20Facts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20millennials%20are%20marrying%20later%20than%20past%20generations%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrjesscarbino.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Jess%20Carbino%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20sociologist%20for%20Tinder%20and%20Bumble%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20If%20boomers%20followed%20more%20of%20a%20uniform%20timeline%20%E2%80%94%20get%20married%20and%20have%20kids%20in%20your%2020s%20%E2%80%94%20millennials%20are%20hitting%20those%20milestones%20at%20different%20ages%2C%20or%20not%20at%20all.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20this%20in-between%20period%20for%20these%20individuals%20who%20are%20choosing%20to%20be%20childless%2C%26quot%3B%20Carbino%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandra%20Kushnir%2C%2032%2C%20grew%20up%20in%20Utah%2C%20where%20her%20closest%20childhood%20friends%20now%20have%20families.%20The%20difference%20in%20lifestyles%20and%20schedules%20makes%20it%20hard%20to%20plan%20activities%20she'd%20love%20to%20do%20with%20them%2C%20such%20as%20group%20vacations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20moved%20to%20LA%20with%20her%20husband%20to%20focus%20on%20their%20careers%20and%20find%20friends%20with%20similar%20lifestyles.%20But%20while%20they%20have%20plenty%20of%20childless%20single%20and%20coupled%20friends%2C%20that%20doesn't%20always%20translate%20to%20understanding%2C%20either.%20Some%20are%20%26quot%3Bstill%20doing%20drugs%20and%20drinking%20and%20going%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Kushnir%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20that%20anymore%2C%20but%20we%20also%20don't%20have%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c52e2fce-c22d-4b30-ae79-1c5d59713f28%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20creative%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20parent%20friends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it's%20hard%20to%20be%20as%20spontaneous%20with%20friends%20who%20have%20kids%2C%20DINK%20couples%20have%20to%20make%20some%20adjustments.%20Gonzalez%20and%20her%20husband%20travel%20to%20their%20friends'%20homes%20a%20few%20times%20a%20year%20instead%20of%20meeting%20halfway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Alexander%2C%2035%2C%20said%20she%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20travel%20with%20friends'%20kids%2C%20such%20as%20an%20upcoming%20trip%20to%20Disney%20Paris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20with%20kids%20can't%20just%20go%20do%20something%20at%20the%20last%20minute%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Seattle%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20probably%20the%20biggest%20thing%20we've%20had%20to%20shift%2C%20is%20finding%20friends%20who%20have%20more%20availability%20to%20maybe%20just%20drop%20things%20and%20go%20do%20something.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20to%20tell%20people%2C%20'I%20still%20want%20to%20be%20in%20your%20life%2C'%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20added.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20I%20do%20think%20that%20there's%20this%20idea%20that%20once%20you%20have%20kids%2C%20you%20can't%20find%20any%20overlap.%20And%20I%20don't%20really%20think%20that's%20true.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJess%20Lorimer%2C%20based%20in%20Southhampton%2C%20UK%2C%20said%20there%20are%20pluses%20to%20being%20the%20child-free%20friends%2C%20such%20as%20having%20disposable%20income%20and%20additional%20energy.%20Childless%20people%20like%20her%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20the%20fun%20auntie%20uncle%20energy%20that%20you%20might%20not%20always%20be%20able%20to%20be%20as%20the%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20Lorimer%2C%2033%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20She%20enjoys%20going%20on%20trips%20with%20her%20parent%20friends%20and%20helping%20their%20kids%20build%20sandcastles%20or%20bringing%20back%20gifts%20from%20vacations%20for%20the%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292e844b2-d178-41db-9468-cb1c10a97da8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20new%20friends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20old%20friends%20being%20busy%20with%20kids%20can%20leave%20social%20gaps%20for%20DINKs%20that%20aren't%20always%20easy%20to%20fill.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchris-duffy-making-friends-as-an-adult-can-be-hard-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMaking%20friends%20in%20one's%2030s%3C%2Fa%3E%20comes%20with%20unique%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20gets%20busier%2C%26quot%3B%20Gonzalez%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20more%20responsibilities%2C%20it's%20much%20harder%20to%20keep%20the%20same%20level%20of%20friendship%20where%20you're%20seeing%20each%20other%20multiple%20times%20a%20week.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarbino%20said%20that%20DINKs%20have%20to%20look%20for%20groups%20or%20organizations%20where%20people%20are%20roughly%20the%20same%20age%20(or%20in%20the%20same%20life%20stage)%2C%20share%20the%20same%20general%20interests%2C%20and%20are%20also%20open%20and%20available%20for%20new%20friends%2C%20too%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20gets%20tougher%20as%20people%20get%20older%2C%20settle%20into%20their%20schedules%2C%20and%20stick%20to%20their%20core%20friend%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKushnir%20and%20her%20husband%20met%20some%20couple%20friends%20through%20Honeymoon%20Israel%2C%20a%2010-day%20trip%20that%20she%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bbirthright%26quot%3B%20for%20Jewish%20and%20interfaith%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20criteria%20where%20you%20have%20to%20be%202-5%20years%20into%20your%20relationship%2C%20engaged%20or%20married%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they%20kind%20of%20try%20to%20match%20couples%20that%20are%20in%20the%20same%20life%20stage%20as%20you%20on%20the%20trip.%26quot%3B%20They%20met%20multiple%20people%20just%20like%20them%3A%20interfaith%20couples%20with%20no%20kids%20(four%20of%20those%20couples%20went%20on%20to%20have%20kids%20around%20the%20same%20time).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKushnir%20said%20they%20also%20made%20like-minded%20friends%20by%20continuing%20to%20show%20up%20to%20a%20local%20dog%20park.%20They%20befriended%20other%20child-free%20couples%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-dinkwad-double-income-no-kids-dog-tiktok-trend-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDINKWADs%3C%2Fa%3E%20(DINKs%20With%20a%20Dog)%2C%20people%20who%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20share%20some%20of%20the%20same%20priorities%20and%20routines%20as%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221179%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20on%20the%20beach%20with%20their%20dog%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d213ec43b5e59d16b730da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221534%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESandra%20Kushnir%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20their%20dog.%3Cp%3ESandra%20Kushnir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20DINKs%20have%20had%20to%20examine%20their%20ideas%20around%20friendship%20in%20their%2030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20just%20think%20of%20friendship%20as%20all%20or%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexander%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20really%20look%20at%20our%20friendships%2C%20we%20have%20people%20we%20go%20to%20for%20work%20problems%2C%20people%20we%20travel%20with%20%E2%80%94%20certain%20friends%20might%20fill%20a%20lot%20of%20buckets%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20needs.%26quot%3B%20When%20some%20of%20her%20longtime%20travel%20buddies%20now%20had%20kids%2C%20she%20said%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20adjusted%20to%20inviting%20new%20friends%20on%20vacations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGonzalez%2C%20who's%20met%20friends%20through%20work%20and%20some%20interest%20groups%2C%20made%20some%20unexpected%20connections%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fage-gap-friendship-best-friend-two-decades-older-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eage-gap%20friendships%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20parents%20of%20older%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20their%20kids%20are%20older%2C%20they%20can%20stay%20home%20alone%20or%20their%20kids%20also%20have%20their%20own%20events%20and%20social%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20frees%20the%20parents%20up%20a%20little%20bit%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22af69eb24-133f-4278-a1b6-1462160c3603%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinding%20deeper%20friendships%20than%20the%20ones%20forged%20in%20their%2020s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDINKs%20deal%20with%20a%20big%20transition%20period%20once%20most%20of%20their%20friends%20start%20having%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20one's%20friends%20having%20kids%20is%20a%20big%20transition%20period.%20%26quot%3BYou%20suddenly%20realize%20that%20you%20are%20not%20the%20priority%20anymore%20as%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20Lorimer%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20readjust%20your%20expectations%20of%20what%20your%20friends%20can%20reasonably%20manage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20readjustment%20can%20also%20bring%20DINKs%20and%20parent%20friends%20closer%20together.%20Lorimer%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildfree-but-still-like-kids-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehaving%20so%20many%20friends%20with%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20(or%20trying%20for%20them)%20exposed%20her%20and%20her%20husband%20to%20conversations%20they%20otherwise%20wouldn't%20have%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20friends%20talking%20about%20fertility%2C%20and%20we%20have%20work%20colleagues%20talking%20about%20infertility%20and%20miscarriages%2C%20which%20are%20just%20life%20experiences%20that%20we%20won't%20ever%20go%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20been%20interesting%20from%20an%20empathy%20perspective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Kushnir%20lives%20far%20from%20her%20childhood%20friends%2C%20she%20still%20keeps%20in%20contact%20with%20them.%20%26quot%3BThey%20ask%20me%20questions%20about%20my%20life%20and%20update%20me%2C%20and%20I%20share%20some%20of%20my%20fears%20about%20having%20a%20family%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20friendships%20also%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20go%20deeper.%20Alexander%20tries%20to%20stay%20open%20to%20all%20new%20connections%2C%20including%20an%20older%20woman%20in%20her%20neighborhood.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20see%20each%20other%2C%20we'll%20sit%20at%20the%20same%20table%20at%20our%20neighborhood%20coffee%20shop%20and%20we'll%20chat%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20DINKS%20like%20Kushnir%20who%20eventually%20want%20to%20become%20parents%2C%20having%20more%20time%20means%20finding%20a%20stronger%20network%20of%20support%20for%20when%20she%20does%20have%20kids.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20like%20to%20go%20through%20being%20pregnant%20and%20having%20a%20kid%20with%20somebody%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20and%20is%20trying%20to%20time%20her%20pregnancy%20with%20one%20of%20her%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2295d83903-08ce-4fe8-9be2-d8828973cd09%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoing%20against%20the%20grain%20has%20its%20perks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeen-together-for-19-years-and-we-are-childfree-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20child-free%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20become%20less%20taboo%20over%20the%20years%2C%20some%20DINKs%20still%20feel%20judged%2C%20and%20roll%20their%20eyes%20at%20the%20stereotype.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20seem%20to%20think%20that%20dinks%20are%20wandering%20around%20with%20Gucci%20handbags%20and%20spending%20all%20of%20their%20money%20and%20time%20frivolously%2C%26quot%3B%20Lorimer%20said.%20But%20she%20siad%20she%20spends%20a%20lot%20of%20her%20time%20on%20work%2C%20charitable%20causes%2C%20and%20supporting%20her%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20best%20things%20that%20I%20found%20about%20being%20child-free%2C%20particularly%20by%20choice%2C%20is%20that%20I've%20been%20able%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20sympathetic%20to%20my%20friends%20who%20perhaps%20aren't%20child-free%20by%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She's%20not%20judgmental%20of%20friends%20who%20are%20struggling%20to%20conceive%20or%20who%20question%20having%20children%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20laughing%20and%20working%20on%20a%20laptop%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d20ffa392a3bda9f23b753%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJessica%20Lorimer%20said%20she%20spends%20much%20of%20her%20time%20working%20on%20charitable%20causes.%3Cp%3EKate%20Sharp%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20much%20harder%20to%20have%20frequent%20interaction%20due%20to%20diverging%20lifestyles%2C%20Alexander%20sees%20the%20%26quot%3Bsmaller%20value%26quot%3B%20in%20friendships.%20She's%20ok%20with%20having%20a%20friend%20solely%20to%20go%20paddleboarding%20with%20or%20to%20a%20cookbook%20signing%2C%20and%20she'll%20also%20try%20to%20invite%20those%20friends%20to%20bigger%20bonding%20experiences%2C%20such%20as%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20had%20a%20pretty%20easy%20time%20making%20friends%2C%20because%20I'll%20kind%20of%20just%20allow%20it%20to%20build%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDINKs%20might%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20where%20they%20belong%20in%20their%20parent-friends'%20lives%20and%20in%20their%20communities%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20conventions%20change%2C%20individuals%20will%20be%20able%20to%20adopt%20sort%20of%20a%20new%20model%20of%20what%20social%20life%20looks%20like%20among%20individuals%20who%20have%20smaller%20families%20and%20who%20choose%20to%20not%20have%20children%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Carbino%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELorimer%2C%20who%20has%20two%20godchildren%2C%20said%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20work%20%26quot%3Bvery%20hard%26quot%3B%20to%20stay%20involved%20in%20their%20friends'%20lives.%20They%20always%20bring%20back%20presents%20from%20trips%20and%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20special%20occasions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20turn%2C%20they've%20received%20deep%20understanding%20right%20back.%20%26quot%3BWe%20choose%20to%20be%20child-free%2C%20and%20we've%20always%20been%20really%20honest%20about%20that%20with%20our%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20very%20fortunate%20that%20our%20friends%20have%20taken%20the%20time%20to%20understand%20why%20we%20wouldn't%20make%20the%20same%20decisions%20around%20children%20that%20they%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdinks-childfree-couples-friends-millennial-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725358982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d211c3392a3bda9f23b85c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%2