2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-living-home-challenging-societal-norms-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecoming%20home%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20only%20a%20few%20years%2C%20but%20I%20can%20also%20appreciate%20that%20independence%20could%20be%20something%20he'd%20enjoy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225cb3dba7-06a5-42b9-b730-f8514e4d65a1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20one%20con%20to%20taking%20a%20gap%20year%20doesn't%20seem%20that%20bad%20to%20me%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20some%2C%20one%20big%2C%20obvious%20con%20for%20a%20gap%20year%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-school-seniors-considering-pandemic-gap-year-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estarting%20college%20a%20year%20later%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20therefore%20graduating%20a%20year%20later%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20every%20student%20graduates%20in%20a%20neat%20four%20years%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20and%20career%20paths%20are%20constantly%20changing%20and%20morphing.%20Also%2C%20as%20someone%20who%20took%20five%20years%20to%20graduate%20from%20college%20(and%20was%20married%20and%20four%20months%20pregnant%20when%20I%20finally%20did)%2C%20I%20can%20say%20that%20the%20extra%20year%20had%20little%20to%20no%20impact%20on%20my%20career%20trajectory.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20son%20has%20mentioned%20that%20he%20already%20has%20friends%20both%20older%20and%20younger%20than%20him.%20Of%20course%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20if%20he%20will%20go%20to%20college%20with%20those%20friends%20at%20this%20point%20(but%20they%20are%20very%20close-knit%2C%20so%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20surprised%20if%20that%20happens).%20He%20doesn't%20seem%20too%20bothered%20about%20the%20idea%20of%20starting%20college%20at%2019%20instead%20of%2018%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20it%20would%20make%20much%20of%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C