t%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELaura%20Mae%20Martin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20encouraging%20more%20people%20to%20feel%20JOMO%20%E2%80%94%20the%20joy%20of%20missing%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20is%20that%20sometimes%20we%20are%20actually%20even%20happier%20when%20we%20miss%20that%20email%2C%20text%2C%20podcast%2C%20or%20programs%20we%20didn't%20really%20want%20to%20follow%20through%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said%20in%20her%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BUptime%3A%20A%20Practical%20Guide%20to%20Personal%20Productivity%20and%20Wellbeing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Martin%2C%20whose%20job%20is%20helping%20Google's%20top%20leaders%20achieve%20maximum%20productivity%2C%20she%20began%20practicing%20JOMO%20via%20a%20weekly%20tradition%20she%20first%20started%20with%20her%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20Tuesday%2C%20they%20would%20put%20away%20their%20devices%20at%20night%20and%20instead%20do%20other%20activities%20and%20hobbies%20like%20board%20games%20and%20spending%20time%20outdoors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20Tuesdays%20ended%20up%20being%20some%20of%20our%20favorite%20nights%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartin%20said%20those%20unplugged%20hours%20are%20crucial%20to%20recharge%20your%20brain%2C%20which%20ultimately%20leads%20to%20more%20productivity%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20And%20that%20mental%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20time%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20getting%20shorter%20and%20shorter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20DataReportal's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatareportal.com%2Freports%2Fdigital-2024-global-overview-report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20Digital%20Global%20Overview%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20annual%20publication%20on%20worldwide%20digital%20trends%2C%20internet%20users%20in%20the%20US%20spend%20an%20average%20of%207%20hours%20and%203%20minutes%20daily%20on%20any%20device.%20Increased%20screen%20time%20has%20also%20been%20linked%20to%20potential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscreen-time-effects-health-vision-staring-at-screens-bad-for-you-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evision%20damage%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20poorer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadults-who-used-smartphones-younger-teens-report-more-distress-now-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%20health%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartin's%20personal%20success%20with%20the%20challenge%20inspired%20her%20to%20bring%20the%20tradition%20to%20the%20Google%20offices.%20However%2C%20asking%20tech%20bros%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20their%20tech%20%E2%80%94%20even%20for%20just%20a%20night%20%E2%80%94%20required%20a%20strategic%20introduction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20Swiss-cheese%20it%20and%20decided%20to%20focus%20on%20a%20manageable%20goal%2C%20like%20turning%20off%20the%20phone%20for%20a%20few%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday%20was%20also%20another%20calculated%20choice.%20Martin%20said%20she%20deliberately%20named%20her%20challenge%20with%20snappy%20alliteration%20and%20clear%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EPick%20one%20night%20a%20week%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20so%20much%20less%20powerful%20than%20%3Cem%3ENo-Tech%20Tuesday%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20catchy%3B%20it%20gives%20direction%2C%20rhythm%2C%20and%20structure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20Martin%20implemented%20the%20challenge%20in%20January%2C%20since%20starting%20a%20new%20initiative%20may%20%26quot%3Bfeel%20more%20natural%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%20rather%20than%20a%20random%20month.%20She%20said%20people%20are%20%26quot%3Bwilling%20to%20make%20a%20bigger%20change%20since%20it's%20the%20start%20of%20something%20new.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Googlers%20were%20very%20willing.%20For%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20Martin%20said%20over%202%2C500%20people%20have%20accepted%20the%20challenge%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlmost%20all%20the%20feedback%20I%