0from%20a%20subset%20of%20asset%20owners%2C%20whereas%20I'd%20say%20the%20interest%20in%20private%20credit%2C%20private%20equity%2C%20real%20estate%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20is%20more%20uniform%20across%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20is%20getting%20ready%20for%20the%20next%20crisis%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20sure%20governance%20is%20ready%20to%20be%20opportunistic.%20A%20quick%20walkthrough%20of%20recent%20history%20shows%20that%20in%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis%2C%20you%20could%20get%20great%20private%20equity%20portfolios%20of%2060%20cents%20on%20the%20dollar%20for%20about%20three%20to%20six%20months%20and%20great%20deals%20on%20distressed%20debt%20for%20about%20three%20to%20six%20months.%20For%20high-yield%20debt%20in%20the%20COVID%20drawdown%2C%20it%20was%20about%20three%20weeks.%20In%20the%20gilts%20crisis%2C%20it%20was%20about%20three%20days.%20So%20the%20opportunity%20to%20be%20opportunistic%20seems%20to%20be%20shrinking%20as%20we%20have%20these%20crises%2C%20and%20having%20your%20governance%20ready%20%E2%80%94at%20least%20to%20rebalance%2C%20but%20ideally%20to%20be%20opportunistic%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20focus%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20institutional%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20sense%20that%20we%20haven't%20had%20a%20real%20crisis%20in%20a%20long%20time.%20The%20COVID%20drawdown%20was%20actually%20short-lived.%20We%2C%20collectively%20as%20a%20society%2C%20threw%20so%20much%20monetary%20and%20fiscal%20stimulus%20at%20it.%20While%20the%20virus%20was%20horrible%2C%20the%20economy%20didn't%20come%20to%20a%20halt%2C%20at%20least%20in%20developed%20markets.%20The%20policy%20response%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20their%20governance%20ready%20to%20be%20opportunistic%20fast%20but%20also%20ready%20for%2C%20say%2C%20a%20three-year%20period%20when%20the%20stock%20market's%20down%2045%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2242447b79-0347-4bf4-a980-d0c9fff19632%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrivate%20credit%20has%20been%20the%20flavor%20of%20the%20month%20for%20roughly%20a%20year%20now%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20like%20institutions%20can't%20get%20enough.%20Do%20you%20have%20any%20worries%20about%20the%20space%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20a%20lot%20more%20worried%20about%20the%20possible%20impact%20of%20a%20widespread%20crisis%20on%20the%20private%20credit%20sub-asset%20classes%20last%20October%20than%20we%20are%20today.%20When%20you%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Greenwich%20Economic%20Forum%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-credit-toast-of-the-town-greenwich-economic-forum-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elast%20fall%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20about%20half%20the%20people%20that%20got%20onstage%20were%20telling%20us%20that%20the%20US%2010-year%20yield%20was%20going%20to%20go%20to%207.5%25%2C%20the%20US%20government%20budget%20deficit%20and%20structural%20deficits%20weren't%20sustainable%2C%20that%20the%20US%20dollar%20would%20lose%20its%20role%20as%20a%20global%20reserve%20currency%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20this%20was%20during%20a%20week%20when%20Speaker%20McCarthy%20found%20a%20way%20to%20keep%20the%20government%20open%2C%20but%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20speakership.%20We%20were%20talking%20about%20trying%20to%20get%20inflation%20under%20control%20globally%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20clear%20that%20the%20monetary%20authorities%20could%20do%20that.%20The%20consensus%20wisdom%20was%20that%20to%20do%20that%2C%20they'd%20have%20to%20put%20us%20into%20recession%20with%20significant%20unemployment%2C%20so%20then%20you%20lose%20consumer%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20today%2C%20we've%20got%20stocks%20at%20all-time%20highs.%20We've%20got%20bond%20yields%20well-behaved.%20We've%20got%20the%20Fed%20Chairman%20going%20to%20Jackson%20Hole%20and%20saying%2C%20'Okay%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20cut.'%20So%20the%20prospect%20of%20an%20immediate%20crisis%20is%20a%20lot%20more%20relaxed%2C%20so%20the%20idea%20that%20these%20asset%20classes%20are%20going%