54a40e7739%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMatt%20Harrison%20Clough%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20afternoon%20this%20summer%2C%20a%20tech%20employee%20I'll%20call%20Dylan%20received%20a%20meeting%20invitation%20out%20of%20the%20blue.%20Labeled%20%26quot%3Bprivate%20and%20confidential%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20mandatory%20call%20was%20set%20for%2010%20the%20next%20morning.%20A%20follow-up%20email%20instructed%20him%20to%20come%20into%20the%20office%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etake%20the%20meeting%2C%20and%20to%20bring%20his%20ID%20badge%20and%20company-issued%20laptop%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20he%20received%20the%20next%20morning%20was%20no%20surprise%3A%20The%20company%20had%20been%20quietly%20axing%20employees%20for%20months.%20He%20surrendered%20his%20badge%20and%20laptop%2C%20signed%20a%20form%2C%20and%20was%20shown%20the%20door.%20As%20he%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewalked%20the%20long%20way%20home%2C%20he%20began%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebrainstorm%20a%20plan%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-recession-high-salary-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20search%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20lay%20ahead.%20Action%20item%20No.%201%3A%20Should%20he%20turn%20on%20the%20Open%20to%20Work%20banner%20on%20LinkedIn%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20banner%20or%20not%20to%20banner%3A%20The%20question%20has%20become%20an%20agonizing%20rite%20of%20passage%20for%20the%20newly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-report-labor-market-hiring-layoffs-quits-recession-sahm-rule-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunemployed%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20Dylan.%20In%20theory%2C%20it's%20supposed%20to%20signal%20recruiters%20that%20you'd%20welcome%20their%20outreach%2C%20and%20let%20your%20professional%20network%20know%20that%20you'd%20appreciate%20their%20leads.%20But%20many%20worry%20that%20the%20banner%20comes%20off%20as%20a%20show%20of%20weakness%20or%20desperation%20%E2%80%94%20the%20digital-age%20equivalent%20of%20standing%20on%20the%20sidewalk%20wearing%20a%20sandwich%20board%20that%20reads%20Job%20Wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20a%20public%20shaming%2C%26quot%3B%20Dylan%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20saying%2C%20'I'm%20a%20loser.'%20But%20maybe%20this%20is%20a%20necessary%20tool%20in%20the%20tool%20kit%20that%20I'm%20just%20refusing%20to%20use%20out%20of%20pride%20or%20ego.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%20I've%20been%20following%20the%20heated%20debates%20about%20Open%20to%20Work.%20On%20LinkedIn%2C%20on%20Reddit%2C%20on%20X%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-open-to-work-tag-red-flag-desperation-recruiter-says-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20very%20pages%20of%20this%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20arguments%20for%20and%20against%20the%20feature%20are%20everywhere.%20Some%20consider%20the%20banner%20a%20job%20seeker's%20best%20friend.%20Others%20view%20it%20as%20peak%20cringe%2C%20an%20instant%20turnoff%20for%20potential%20employers.%20Both%20sides%20talk%20about%20it%20with%20the%20kind%20of%20conviction%20usually%20reserved%20for%20hot-button%20political%20issues%2C%20like%20abortion%20rights%20or%20gun%20control.%20One%20hater%20called%20it%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20240620123904%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.kornferry.com%2Finsights%2Fthis-week-in-leadership%2Fthe-new-unemployables-a-scary-future%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20kiss%20of%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3B%20another%20likened%20it%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F03%2F11%2Fred-flags-recruiters-look-out-for-in-job-candidates.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easking%20for%20a%20handout%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Few%20things%2C%20it%20would%20seem%2C%20trigger%20our%20complicated%20feelings%20about%20work%20more%20than%20Open%20to%20Work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20misgivings%20about%20the%20banner%20stem%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20still%20a%20relatively%20new%20feature.%20LinkedIn%20first%20rolled%20it%20out%20in%20June%202020%2C%20when%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20Americans%20found%20themselves%20newly%20unemployed%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20By%20then%2C%20more%20than%2030%20million%20users%20had%20already%20used%20a%20feature%20on%20the%20platform%20to%20privately%20signal%20recruiters%20that%20they%20were%20open%20to%20work.%20Now%20LinkedIn%20was%20making%20it%20possible%20to%20make%20that%20declaration%20public.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20your%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20platform's%20chief%20product%20officer%20announced%20in%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fblog%2Fmember%2Fproduct%2Fnew-features-to-give-and-get-help-from-your-community%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20blog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Bjust%20one%20person%20opening%20a%20door%20can%20make%20all%20the%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20feature%20wasn't%20subtle.%20The%20banner%2C%20which%20shows%20up%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20your%20profile%20picture%2C%20blares%20%23OPENTOWORK%20in%20bold%20white%20letters%20on%20a%20bright%20green%20background.%20And%20because%20it's%20stamped%20on%20your%20headshot%2C%20it%20becomes%20the%20most%20visible%20feature%20of%20your%20profile.%20When%20you%20post%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20when%20you%20comment%20on%20someone%20else's%20post%2C%20when%20you%20show%20up%20in%20a%20search%2C%20the%20Open%20to%20Work%20label%20relentlessly%20hugs%20the%20contours%20of%20your%20face.%20It's%20designed%20to%20make%20the%20news%20hyperpublic%2C%20to%20mass-broadcast%20your%20work%20status%20to%20as%20many%20people%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20few%20months%20after%20LinkedIn%20introduced%20the%20banner%20that%20I%20started%20to%20look%20for%20work%20myself.%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20smart%20feature%2C%20but%20I%20couldn't%20imagine%20using%20it.%20There%20was%20something%20visceral%20and%20incongruous%20about%20the%20hashtag%20framing%20my%20big%20wide%20grin%2C%20as%20if%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20was%20out%20of%20work%20was%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20about%20me.%20I%20knew%20I%20shouldn't%2C%20but%20I%20often%20found%20myself%20wincing%20when%20former%20colleagues%20and%20college%20classmates%20sported%20the%20banner.%20%3Cem%3EOof%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20would%20think.%20%3Cem%3EThey%20must%20be%20really%20struggling.%3C%2Fem%3E%20It%20felt%20like%20catching%20a%20glimpse%20of%20their%20private%20suffering%20I%20wasn't%20supposed%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20array%20of%20blue%20eyeballs%20looking%20towards%20a%20green%20colored%20eyeball%20labeled%20%26quot%3BOpenforwork%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8de531aa2ac29ee33d3fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20worry%20they'll%20be%20judged%20for%20sporting%20the%20banner.%20%26quot%3BIt%20invites%20a%20lot%20of%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20one%20job%20seeker.%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20what%20did%20he%20do%3F%20Did%20he%20have%20an%20HR%20issue%3F%20Did%20he%20assault%20someone%3F%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EMatt%20Harrison%20Clough%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELots%20of%20job%20seekers%20say%20they're%20perfectly%20comfortable%20using%20the%20banner.%20A%20data%20scientist%20cheerily%20told%20me%20he%20isn't%20easily%20embarrassed.%20A%20business-development%20professional%20said%20she%20feels%20that%20people%20who%20find%20the%20banner%20cringeworthy%20are%20%26quot%3Bstuck%20in%20the%20past.%26quot%3B%20In%20July%20alone%2C%20according%20to%20LinkedIn%2C%2040%20million%20users%20were%20letting%20their%20Open%20to%20Work%20flag%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20most%20of%20the%20people%20I%20talked%20to%20expressed%20hesitation%20about%20the%20banner.%20Several%20compared%20it%20to%20a%20scarlet%20letter%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that's%20digitally%20tattooed%20on%20your%20face%2C%20rather%20than%20sewn%20on%20your%20dress.%20Whatever%20the%20banner's%20intentions%2C%20it%20can%20serve%20to%20amplify%20the%20sense%20of%20shame%20that%20often%20comes%20from%20being%20unemployed.%20%26quot%3BIt%20invites%20a%20lot%20of%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dylan%2C%20the%20laid-off%20tech%20worker.%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20what%20did%20he%20do%3F%20Did%20he%20have%20an%20HR%20issue%3F%20Did%20he%20assault%20someone%20at%20work%3F%20Did%20something%20nefarious%20go%20down%3F%26quot%3B%20So%20far%2C%20he's%20told%20only%20his%20mom%20and%20closest%20friends%20about%20his%20job%20loss.%20To%20him%2C%20declaring%20yourself%20Open%20to%20Work%20is%20to%20brand%20yourself%20as%20Open%20to%20Dishonor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recruiting%20executive%20I'll%20call%20Rachel%20has%20been%20more%20open%20about%20her%20situation.%20As%20soon%20as%20she%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20she%20reached%20out%20to%20a%20hundred%20of%20her%20contacts%20to%20let%20them%20know%20she%20was%20looking%20for%20work.%20But%20even%20she%20has%20waffled%20on%20using%20the%20banner.%20She%20doesn't%20look%20down%20on%20candidates%20for%20using%20it%20%E2%80%94%20but%20because%20she%20has%20read%20so%20many%20diatribes%20against%20it%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20she%20doesn't%20trust%20other%20recruiters%20to%20be%20as%20open-minded%20about%20it.%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20the%20impression%20that%20some%20people%20look%20at%20the%20badge%20as%20if%20you're%20a%20homeless%20person%20sitting%20on%20the%20corner%20with%20a%20freaking%20cardboard%20sign%20that%20reads%2C%20Will%20Work%20for%20Food%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20I%20struggle.%20I%20would%20hate%20to%20be%20passed%20on%20because%20a%20recruiter%20lazily%20looked%20at%20my%20badge%20and%20judged%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20IT%20manager%20I'll%20call%20Connor%20was%20also%20convinced%20by%20the%20online%20commentary%20to%20forgo%20the%20banner.%20%26quot%3BThe%20majority%20of%20the%20opinions%20were%20'don't%20do%20it%2C'%20because%20recruiters%20don't%20want%20desperate%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20belief%20that%20the%20best%20employees%20are%20snatched%20up%20right%20away.%20If%20I%20turn%20it%20on%2C%20I'm%20signaling%20that%20I'm%20automatically%20not%20one%20of%20the%20best%20and%20brightest.%26quot%3B%20But%20he's%20bitter%20that%20using%20the%20green%20banner%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20red%20flag.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20bizarre%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20observed.%20%26quot%3BSaying%20'we%20can't%20hire%20you%20because%20you%20said%20you%20want%20a%20job'%20is%20like%20saying%20'we%20can't%20feed%20you%20because%20you%20said%20you're%20hungry.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20are%20job%20seekers%20right%20to%20assume%20that%20recruiters%20will%20shun%20them%20for%20coming%20out%20as%20unemployed%20on%20LinkedIn%3F%20To%20my%20surprise%2C%20only%20one%20of%20the%20eight%20recruiters%20I%20spoke%20with%20said%20the%20banner%20gives%20him%20pause%20about%20a%20candidate%2C%20viewing%20it%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20%26quot%3Bpassivity%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20face%20of%20a%20stalled%20search.%20Two%20recruiters%20said%20they%20feel%20neutral%20about%20it.%20The%20rest%20said%20that%2C%20if%20anything%2C%20they%20actually%20seek%20out%20Open%20to%20Workers.%20Some%20even%20use%20LinkedIn%20Recruiter%2C%20a%20premium%20version%20of%20the%20platform%2C%20to%20prioritize%20candidates%20who%20use%20the%20banner.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20if%20I%20approach%20them%2C%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20interested%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20recruiter%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20responsive%2C%20more%20open%20to%20talking.%26quot%3B%20Recruiters%20also%20know%20that%20Open%20to%20Work%20candidates%20are%20available%20for%20interviews%20%E2%80%94%20and%20can%20start%20a%20new%20job%20without%20having%20to%20give%20notice.%20%26quot%3BThat%20helps%20me%20move%20my%20process%20along%20more%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20recruiter%20explained.%20%26quot%3BMy%20hiring%20managers%20want%20their%20roles%20filled%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20was%20skeptical.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2020-08078-000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStudies%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehave%20found%20that%20recruiters%20tend%20to%20discriminate%20against%20the%20unemployed%2C%20offering%20substantially%20lower%20callback%20rates%20for%20out-of-work%20candidates%20than%20for%20those%20with%20a%20job.%20And%20critics%20of%20Open%20to%20Work%20often%20advise%20candidates%20to%20steer%20clear%20of%20the%20banner%2C%20calling%20it%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F10%2F31%2Fdont-use-linkedins-open-to-work-sign-says-former-google-recruiter.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20red%20flag%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20embarrassing%20display%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F03%2F11%2Fred-flags-recruiters-look-out-for-in-job-candidates.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epick-me%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20So%20I%20pressed%20the%20recruiters%20I%20spoke%20with%20on%20this%20point.%20Are%20you%3Cem%3E%20sure%20%3C%2Fem%3Eyou%20don't%20judge%20bannered%20workers%2C%20even%20just%20a%20tiny%20bit%3F%20Don't%20you%20worry%20that%20they're%20out%20of%20work%20for%20good%20reason%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20my%20job%20to%20ask%20questions%2C%20to%20find%20out%20why%20they're%20looking%20for%20a%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20recruiter%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BA%20proper%20recruiter%20won't%20make%20decisions%20based%20on%20assumptions.%20Nowadays%2C%20especially%20with%20all%20the%20layoffs%2C%20you%20really%20don't%20know%20why%20people%20are%20out%20of%20a%20job.%20Layoffs%20can%20be%20completely%20random.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20recruiter%20hates%20that%20candidates%20are%20being%20warned%20against%20declaring%20themselves%20Open%20to%20Work.%20%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20me%20grind%20my%20teeth%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20so%20much%20misinformation%20out%20there.%20These%20messages%20are%20typically%20coming%20from%20someone%20who's%20never%20worked%20in%20recruiting%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20a%20'career%20coaching%20guru%2C'%20or%20whatever%20job%20title%20they%20like%20to%20use%20to%20market%20themselves.%20It's%20unfortunate%2C%20because%20it%20gets%20to%20a%20point%20where%20job%20seekers%20don't%20know%20what%20advice%20to%20listen%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20these%20banner-friendly%20recruiters%20are%20in%20the%20minority.%20In%20a%20survey%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tealhq.com%2Fpost%2Fcareer-empowerment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETeal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20makes%20software%20for%20job%20seekers%2C%20only%209%25%20of%20recruiters%20and%20hiring%20managers%20said%20they%20viewed%20the%20banner%20negatively.%20And%20LinkedIn's%20own%20data%20confirms%20that%20listing%20yourself%20as%20Open%20to%20Work%20actually%3Cem%3E%20encourages%20%3C%2Fem%3Erecruiters%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20you.%20People%20who%20turn%20on%20the%20private%20signal%20are%20twice%20as%20likely%20to%20get%20a%20message%20from%20a%20recruiter%20than%20those%20who%20don't%2C%20the%20platform%20told%20me.%20And%20those%20who%20turn%20on%20the%20public%20banner%20increase%20their%20chances%20by%20nearly%20threefold.%20The%20more%20open%20you%20are%20about%20needing%20a%20job%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20you%20are%20to%20get%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20deeper%20level%2C%20though%2C%20it%20isn't%20recruiters%20that%20everyone%20on%20LinkedIn%20is%20worried%20about.%20After%20all%2C%20every%20job%20seeker%20I%20spoke%20with%20who%20decided%20against%20using%20the%20public%20Open%20to%20Work%20banner%20was%20still%20deploying%20the%20private%20signal%20to%20potential%20employers.%20We%20know%2C%20deep%20down%2C%20that%20recruiters%20are%20professionally%20trained%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20their%20biases.%20But%20our%20peers%3F%20Not%20so%20much.%20The%20real%20reason%20we%20don't%20use%20the%20banner%20is%20that%20we're%20worried%20about%20what%20our%20friends%20and%20colleagues%20will%20think%20of%20us.%20If%20they%20see%20us%20as%20desperate%2C%20or%20feel%20embarrassed%20for%20us%2C%20won't%20that%20make%20them%20less%20likely%20to%20give%20us%20the%20help%20we%20need%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfer%20Sharone%2C%20a%20sociologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Massachusetts%20Amherst%2C%20studies%20long-term%20unemployment%20among%20elite%20professionals.%20For%20his%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobal.oup.com%2Facademic%2Fproduct%2Fthe-stigma-trap-9780190239244%3Fcc%3Dus%26lang%3Den%26%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Stigma%20Trap%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20asked%20alumni%20of%20a%20leading%20business%20school%20what%20they%20would%20do%20if%20they%20were%20contacted%20by%20a%20fellow%20graduate%20who%20was%20hoping%20to%20network%20with%20them.%20At%20first%2C%20they%20were%20eager%20to%20connect.%20But%20when%20Sharone%20added%20that%20the%20graduate%20seeking%20to%20network%20had%20been%20unemployed%20for%20a%20year%2C%20they%20suddenly%20demurred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20unfortunate%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20alum%20told%20Sharone%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20you%20wonder%20if%20there%20is%20something%20going%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20another.%20%26quot%3BMy%20cynicism%20says%20that%20very%20few%20people%20who%20are%20really%20good%20get%20laid%20off%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20probably%20a%20bias%20that's%20unfair.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20attitude%2C%20Sharone%20has%20found%2C%20permeates%20American%20culture.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20alumni%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20in%20our%20society%20has%20this%20unconscious%20bias%20against%20someone%20unemployed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stigma%2C%20he%20says%2C%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20how%20precarious%20the%20modern%20workplace%20has%20become.%20Back%20in%20the%201950s%20and%20'60s%2C%20companies%20almost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enever%20laid%20off%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20get%20the%20ax%2C%20professionals%20had%20to%20be%20really%20bad%20at%20their%20jobs%2C%20or%20do%20something%20beyond%20the%20pale.%20But%20today%2C%20white-collar%20elites%20are%20starting%20to%20learn%20what%20blue-collar%20workers%20already%20know%20through%20long%20and%20bitter%20experience%3A%20that%20you%20can%20lose%20your%20job%20at%20any%20time%2C%20for%20any%20reason%20%E2%80%94%20or%20for%20no%20reason%20at%20all.%20For%20those%20with%20a%20college%20degree%2C%20Sharone%20says%2C%20shunning%20the%20unemployed%20is%20a%20coping%20mechanism%2C%20a%20way%20of%20convincing%20ourselves%20that%20we'll%20remain%20afloat%20in%20a%20rising%20sea%20of%20pink%20slips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20someone%20who's%20college%20educated%20and%20really%20qualified%20and%20experienced%20is%20unemployed%2C%20that's%20a%20scary%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20could%20mean%20%3Cem%3Eanybody%3C%2Fem%3E%20could%20be%20unemployed.%20That%20could%20mean%20%3Cem%3EI%3C%2Fem%3E%20could%20be%20unemployed.%20So%20the%20way%20to%20avoid%20that%20conclusion%20and%20keep%20yourself%20feeling%20calm%20is%20to%20think%2C%20'Well%2C%20maybe%20that%20person%20did%20something%20wrong.'%26quot%3B%20We'd%20rather%20blame%20the%20individual%20than%20the%20system%20%E2%80%94%20because%20blaming%20the%20system%20involves%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20reality%20that%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20we%20do%2C%20we%20could%20lose%20our%20livelihood%20tomorrow.%20In%20an%20employment%20landscape%20full%20of%20fear%20and%20uncertainty%2C%20Open%20to%20Work%20banners%20are%20an%20unwelcome%20reminder%20that%20we%20are%20all%20expendable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20a%20firsthand%20sense%20of%20what%20it%20feels%20like%20to%20use%20the%20Open%20to%20Work%20banner%2C%20I%20forced%20myself%20to%20do%20the%20thing%20I%20avoided%20in%20my%20job%20search%20four%20years%20ago%3A%20I%20turned%20mine%20on.%20From%20the%20start%20it%20made%20me%20deeply%20uncomfortable%2C%20and%20I%20was%20repeatedly%20tempted%20to%20take%20it%20down.%20What%20would%20people%20think%20of%20me%20if%20they%20saw%20me%20as%20unemployed%3F%20Was%20I%20secretly%20being%20pitied%3F%20Or%20worse%2C%20judged%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20way%20to%20know%20for%20sure.%20As%20the%20weeks%20went%20by%2C%20no%20one%20I%20knew%20commented%20on%20my%20new%20status%2C%20except%20for%20a%20colleague%20who%20was%20worried%20that%20I%20had%20left%20Business%20Insider.%20I%20also%20didn't%20hear%20from%20any%20employers%2C%20which%20was%2C%20I'll%20admit%2C%20a%20blow%20to%20my%20ego.%20Instead%2C%20I%20got%20a%20mysterious%20message%20from%20someone%20at%20a%20company%20I%20had%20never%20heard%20of%20touting%20%26quot%3Ban%20amazing%20business%20opportunity.%26quot%3B%20I%20could%20learn%20more%20about%20it%2C%20they%20told%20me%2C%20in%20an%20information%20session%20on%20Zoom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20ball%20and%20chain%20with%20an%20open%20cuff%20labeled%20%26quot%3B%23openforwork%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8dda243b5e59d16b4d033%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20the%20only%20way%20to%20overcome%20the%20stigma%20of%20unemployment%20is%20to%20pierce%20the%20silence%20that%20surrounds%20it.%20%3Cp%3EMatt%20Harrison%20Clough%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20apparently%20a%20common%20experience%20among%20LinkedIn%20users%20who%20deploy%20the%20banner.%20One%20told%20me%20he%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20messages%20from%20recruiters%20about%20lower-pay%20contract%20work%20he%20was%20overqualified%20for.%20He%20also%20got%20at%20least%20one%20scam%20asking%20for%20his%20Social%20Security%20number.%20Another%20job%20seeker%20received%20messages%20from%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20writers%20touting%20their%20services%3B%20one%20quoted%20him%20a%20fee%20of%20%246%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20when%20you're%20out%20of%20work%2C%20it's%20worth%20wading%20through%20a%20bunch%20of%20unwelcome%20responses%20in%20search%20of%20the%20right%20opportunity.%20The%20data%20scientist%20I%20spoke%20with%20said%20the%20banner%20led%20him%20to%20two%20job%20interviews%20%E2%80%94%20including%20one%20with%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20startup.%20And%20the%20business-development%20manager%20I%20spoke%20with%20fared%20even%20better.%20She%20not%20only%20turned%20on%20the%20Open%20to%20Work%20banner%2C%20she%20also%20posted%20a%20few%20paragraphs%20explaining%20what%20she%20was%20looking%20for.%20The%20response%20was%20swift.%20Acquaintances%20shared%20her%20post%20with%20their%20networks%3B%20former%20colleagues%20and%20clients%20introduced%20her%20to%20people%20in%20their%20companies%20who%20were%20hiring.%20She%20got%20several%20interviews%2C%20and%20within%20weeks%20she%20landed%20a%20job.%20The%20owner%20of%20the%20company%20was%20a%20LinkedIn%20connection%20who%20reached%20out%20after%20seeing%20her%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20which%20suggests%20that%2C%20stigma%20aside%2C%20you'll%20be%20missing%20out%20on%20opportunities%20if%20you%20don't%20turn%20on%20the%20public%20banner.%20LinkedIn's%20data%20shows%20that%20public%20Open%20to%20Workers%20get%2040%25%20more%20messages%20from%20LinkedIn%20Recruiter%20than%20those%20who%20use%20only%20the%20private%20signal.%20(One%20recruiter%20told%20me%20they%20consider%20public%20candidates%20more%20serious%20than%20private%20ones%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20already%20have%20jobs%20and%20are%20just%20looking%20around%20for%20something%20better.)%20And%20smaller%20employers%20can't%20afford%20the%20expensive%20premium%20version%20of%20LinkedIn%2C%20which%20costs%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20a%20year.%20If%20you%20want%20the%20little%20guys%20to%20see%20you%2C%20you%20need%20to%20deploy%20the%20public%20flag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20important%2C%20private%20Open%20to%20Workers%20are%20missing%20out%20on%20the%20leads%20they%20might%20get%20from%20former%20colleagues%20and%20clients%20and%20classmates%20%E2%80%94%20the%20people%20who%20already%20know%20what%20a%20great%20hire%20you'd%20be.%20Sure%2C%20some%20of%20your%20contacts%20may%20be%20privately%20judgy%20and%20decline%20to%20help%2C%20as%20Sharone%20found.%20But%20others%20you%20know%20will%20be%20eager%20to%20pitch%20in.%20After%20all%2C%20in%20this%20new%20era%20of%20endless%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20all%20have%20a%20common%20interest%20in%20helping%20our%20friends%20and%20coworkers%20%E2%80%94%20because%2C%20sooner%20or%20later%2C%20we%20may%20be%20the%20ones%20in%20need%20of%20help.%20By%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zippia.com%2Fadvice%2Flayoff-statistics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20estimate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2040%25%20of%20Americans%20have%20been%20laid%20off%20at%20least%20once%20in%20their%20lifetime.%20If%20things%20keep%20going%20the%20way%20they're%20going%2C%20that%20number%20is%20likely%20to%20get%20significantly%20higher%20in%20the%20years%20ahead%2C%20especially%20among%20white-collar%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20isn't%20to%20say%20the%20Open%20to%20Work%20banner%20is%20a%20quick%20fix%20for%20the%20job-search%20blues.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20most%20effective%20strategy%20involves%20old-fashioned%2C%20one-on-one%20networking%2C%20which%20takes%20far%20more%20time%20and%20effort%20than%20a%20simple%20flip%20of%20a%20digital%20switch.%20But%20in%20the%20depths%20of%20unemployment%2C%20every%20lifeline%20counts.%20I%20get%20that%20it's%20uncomfortable%20to%20go%20public%20with%20your%20status.%20I%20was%20relieved%20to%20turn%20off%20my%20banner%20after%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20and%20I%20can%20only%20imagine%20what%20it's%20like%20to%20have%20everyone%20staring%20at%20your%20high-profile%20call%20for%20help%20for%20months%20on%20end.%20But%20when%20the%20stakes%20are%20as%20high%20as%20your%20career%2C%20the%20potential%20upsides%20are%20worth%20whatever%20embarrassment%20it%20might%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20the%20only%20way%20to%20overcome%20the%20societal%20stigma%20of%20unemployment%20is%20to%20pierce%20the%20silence%20that%20has%20surrounded%20it%20for%20so%20long.%20Seven%20years%20ago%2C%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20allegations%20against%20Harvey%20Weinstein%2C%20thousands%20of%20women%20began%20sharing%20their%20own%20experiences%20with%20workplace%20misconduct.%20The%20resulting%20groundswell%20made%20it%20a%20little%20less%20taboo%20to%20talk%20about%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20assault.%20Perhaps%2C%20with%20%23opentowork%2C%20something%20similar%20could%20happen%20to%20the%20way%20we%20talk%20about%20losing%20our%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20not%20yet%20had%20a%20%23metoo%20moment%20about%20layoffs%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sharone.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20this%20takes%20off%2C%20I%20think%20it%20could%20potentially%20take%20away%20some%20of%20the%20stigma.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%3A%20Workers%20of%20the%20world%2C%20be%20Open!%20You%20have%20nothing%20to%20lose%20but%20your%20shame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20artic