3Cstrong%3E2.%20Reduced%20communication%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlston%20said%20any%20level%20of%20reduced%20communication%20or%20vague%20feedback%20from%20your%20manager%20is%20usually%20a%20sign%20of%20an%20impending%20PIP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20lack%20of%20enthusiasm%20even%20on%20their%20part%20could%20be%20a%20red%20flag%20or%20a%20signal%20for%20you%20to%20know%20that%20things%20are%20not%20that%20great%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20change%20like%20this%20is%20particularly%20alarming%20if%20your%20manager%20has%20a%20tendency%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicromanager-boss-being-better-manager-tips-advice-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicromanage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Alston%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20manager%20or%20leader%20who%20at%20one%20point%20was%20constantly%20sharing%20feedback%20and%20communicating%20with%20you%20and%20suddenly%20they%20grow%20silent%2C%20either%20you%20can%20feel%20being%20on%20the%20cutting%20board%2C%20or%20perhaps%20they're%20losing%20enthusiasm%20for%20their%20role%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20for%20me%2C%20I%20would%20always%20say%20lean%20on%20the%20side%20of%20maybe%20you're%20on%20the%20cutting%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20Alston%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a1b0cd82-12fb-4c71-843d-4972aa5d379e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Formal%20feedback%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20start%20getting%20a%20lot%20of%20formal%20feedback%20or%20you're%20asked%20to%20provide%20written%20updated%20communications%2C%20that%20could%20also%20be%20a%20warning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20you%20start%20having%20a%20leader%20who%20puts%20everything%20in%20writing%2C%20especially%20the%20feedback%20and%20negative%20feedback%20they%20have%20for%20you%2C%20that%20is%20always%20the%20number%20one%20telltale%20sign%20that%20a%20PIP%20is%20on%20the%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Alston%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20work%20in%20human%20resources%20are%20often%20told%20to%20document%20everything%2C%20and%20once%20something%20is%20in%20writing%2C%20it%20creates%20a%20paper%20trail%2C%20she%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperformance-improvement-plan-ruin-relationships-better-alternative-pip-hr-strategy-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformally%20warn%20you%20of%20an%20issue%20and%20give%20you%20an%20amount%20of%20days%20to%20fix%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20take%20different%20shapes%2C%20but%20may%20include%20being%20asked%20to%20provide%20frequent%20updates%20or%20the%20date%20for%20when%20you%20plan%20to%20have%20a%20task%20finished%20by%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228ecbdad5-df40-407f-bfbb-a47e3977218c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20signs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlston%20said%20she%20wanted%20to%20do%20all%20that%20was%20possible%20to%20make%20her%20manager%20happy%20again%20to%20avoid%20receiving%20a%20PIP%2C%20which%20she%20didn't%20end%20up%20getting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20recruitment%20agency%2C%20Alston%20tells%20people%20exactly%20what%20to%20do%20if%20they%20see%20these%20signs%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20you're%20over%20communicating%2C%20the%20more%20to%20me%20it%20shows%20that%20you%20understand%20your%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20be%20articulating%20your%20worth%20to%20your%20manager%20and%20how%20serious%20you%20are%20about%20the%20role%20that%20you're%20in%2C%20Alston%20advised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20let%20your%20manager%20second%20guess%20your%20value%2C%20your%20tasks%2C%20or%20your%20commitment%20to%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-a-pip-is-com