oil%20would%20be%20neither%20safe%20nor%20ethical%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20places%20with%20large%20Russian-speaking%20populations%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20volunteer%20and%20do%20something%20working%20with%20the%20large%20Russian-speaking%2C%20new%20Ukrainian%20diaspora.%20I%20had%20spent%20time%20in%20Odesa%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20working%20remotely%20and%20taking%20a%20Russian%20lesson%20every%20lunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20start%20in%20Moldova%20and%20contacted%20a%20few%20local%20and%20international%20organizations%20about%20a%20temporary%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e33ba2e0-989f-4cad-9aaa-e49963a859ae%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20plans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20one-bedroom%20flat%20in%20South%20London%20was%20easy%20to%20sublet.%20I%20kept%20my%20belongings%20in%20storage%20inside%20the%20unit.%20I%20paid%20about%20%C2%A31%2C750%20a%20month%20for%20my%20flat%2C%20including%20utilities%2C%20which%20rose%20to%20%C2%A32%2C050%20that%20September.%20The%20subleasers%20paid%20%C2%A32%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20about%20%C2%A33%2C000%20a%20month%20to%20spend%20and%20a%20budget%20of%20about%20%C2%A3100%20per%20day%2C%20which%20didn't%20require%20me%20to%20dip%20into%20any%20savings%20and%20strictly%20came%20from%20my%20reduced%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20part%20of%20a%20bonus%20from%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20about%20%C2%A35%2C000%2C%20as%20a%20slush%20fund.%20This%20was%20mostly%20for%20airfare%2C%20visas%2C%20and%20visiting%20family%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20not%20backpacking.%20My%20budget%20gave%20me%20the%20flexibility%20to%20find%20comfortable%20accommodation%20and%20the%20best%20mode%20of%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2267ead924-be36-45c3-8522-7ff0c515c829%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EVolunteering%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20my%20last%20day%20at%20work%2C%20I%20set%20an%20out-of-office%20message%20for%20the%20far-off%20January%205%2C%20passing%20off%20every%20unfinished%20project%20to%20my%20colleagues.%20I%20deleted%20my%20inbox%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20the%20first%20time%20in%2012%20years%20that%20I%20had%20no%20ongoing%20tasks%20or%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20into%20my%20sabbatical%2C%20I%20was%20in%20Moldova%20and%20working%20at%20the%20Chisinau%20Dignity%20Centre%2C%20essentially%20a%20food%20bank%20run%20by%20the%20English%20charity%20Refugee%20Support%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20work%20consisted%20of%20two%20basic%20tasks%3A%20ringing%20up%20groceries%20and%20verifying%20documents.%20The%20team%20consisted%20of%20a%20variety%20of%20local%20and%20foreign%20people.%20One%20person%20was%20studying%20to%20be%20a%20sailor%20in%20the%20Ukrainian%20merchant%20marines%3B%20classes%20were%20remote%20because%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20office%20gossip%2C%20we%20wondered%20about%20the%20stories%20of%20those%20who%20came%20in.%20One%20older%20woman%2C%20ceaselessly%20polite%2C%20would%20say%20her%20husband%20was%20%26quot%3Bsleeping%20in%20the%20cemetery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20worked%20hard%2C%20but%20our%20labor%20seemed%20impactful.%20I%20made%20mistakes%2C%20but%20I%20was%20forgiven.%20I%20could%20see%20the%20impact%20of%20our%20work%20much%20quicker%20than%20on%20larger%20corporate%20projects%20with%20larger%20timescales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20have%20stayed%2C%20but%20there%20was%20a%20policy%20against%20volunteering%20for%20over%20a%20month.%20By%20mid-August%2C%20I%20headed%20south%20toward%20the%20Romanian%20border%20and%20continued%20by%20plane%20eastward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228f031d1d-10fe-4fa1-810a-72ab4b141707%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20road%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20next%20four%20months%2C%20I%20lived%20out%20of%20a%20duffel%20bag%2C%20traveling%20from%20the%20desert%20of%20Uzbekistan%20through%20snow-covered%20mountains%20in%20Tajikistan%20to%20dense%20urban%20Chinese%20cities.%20Friends%20and%20relatives%20joined%20me%20for%20a%20few%20sections%2C%20although%20I%20was%20mostly%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELife%20was%20pleasantly%20unstructured.%20I%20made%20radical%20changes%20to%20my%20planned%20itinerary%20and%20kept%20extending%20my%20time%20in%20the%20north%20of%20Kazakhstan%20to%20do%20things%20like%20attend%20a%20hockey%20match%20with%20a%20team%20from%20across%20the%20border%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20saw%20a%20remote%20area%20in%20the%20far%20north%20of%20China%20where%20a%20ski%20resort%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20French%20Alps%20is%20nearing%20completion.%20In%20the%20lobby%20of%20a%20Tajik%20Marriott%2C%20I%20was%20accused%20of%20being%20an%20intelligence%20agent%20when%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20conversation%20over%20a%20Negroni.%20It%20was%20exciting%2C%20random%2C%20and%20fulfilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a782feb-499a-43b7-8b7e-0f189ae022ed%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBack%20again%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%2C%20the%20trip%20seemed%20infinite.%20I%20hadn't%20taken%20more%20than%20two%20weeks%20of%20holiday%20in%20over%2015%20years%2C%20and%2027%20weeks%20at%20the%20start%20seemed%20to%20stretch%20out%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20sudden%20momentum%20of%20existential%20awareness%20in%20the%20fifth%20month%20of%20the%20trip.%20There%20would%20come%20a%20time%20when%20I%20would%20be%20back%20sitting%20at%20a%20shared%20desk%20under%20fluorescent%20lighting%20in%20gray%20London.%20Did%20I%20miss%20the%20work%3F%20Honestly%20no%2C%20but%20perhaps%20that's%20because%20I%20was%20beginning%20to%20forget%20what%20it%20was%20actually%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20to%20put%20it%20out%20of%20my%20mind%20and%20tell%20myself%20it%20would%20be%20fine%20as%20the%20final%20weeks%20wound%20down.%20They%20were%20sweet%20%E2%80%94%20a%20wedding%20in%20central%20India%2C%20a%20week%20on%20the%20beach%20in%20Thailand%2C%20and%20nearly%20a%20month%20seeing%20friends%20who%20had%20children%20and