data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.news.cn%2F20240829%2F35e4b97fe0b2452d93f2241fd2de8554%2Fc.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%227%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.news.cn%2F20240829%2F35e4b97fe0b2452d93f2241fd2de8554%2Fc.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20readout%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%C2%A0following%20the%20conversation%20was%20rather%20positive.%20It%20said%20that%20both%20sides%20had%20%26quot%3Bagreed%20to%20work%20together%20to%20turn%20over%20a%20new%20leaf%20in%20the%20border%20situation%20at%20an%20early%20date%26quot%3B.%20It%20further%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20two%20sides%20exchanged%20in-depth%20views%20on%20relevant%20issues%20in%20border%20areas%2C%20further%20narrowed%20differences%2C%20expanded%20consensus%2C%20and%20agreed%20to%20strengthen%20dialogue%20and%20consultation%2C%20accommodate%20each%20other's%20legitimate%20concerns%2C%20and%20reach%20a%20mutually%20acceptable%20solution%20at%20an%20early%20date.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%228%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F38241%2F31st%2BMeeting%2Bof%2Bthe%2BWorking%2BMechanism%2Bfor%2BConsultation%2B%2BCoordination%2Bon%2BIndiaChina%2BBorder%2BAffairs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%229%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F38241%2F31st%2BMeeting%2Bof%2Bthe%2BWorking%2BMechanism%2Bfor%2BConsultation%2B%2BCoordination%2Bon%2BIndiaChina%2BBorder%2BAffairs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereadout%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%C2%A0was%20much%20more%20contained.%20It%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20two%20sides%20had%20a%20frank%2C%20constructive%20and%20forward-looking%20exchange%20of%20views%20on%20the%20situation%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC)%20to%20narrow%20down%20the%20differences%20and%20find%20early%20resolution%20of%20the%20outstanding%20issues%26quot%3B.%20The%20impact%20of%20these%20meetings%20on%20actual%20resolution%20of%20the%20issues%20in%20Depsang%20and%20Demchok%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Question%20Of%20Chinese%20Investments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Economic%20Survey%20released%20before%20the%20new%20NDA%20government's%20budget%20in%20July%20indicated%20that%20India%20could%20be%20more%20open%20to%20Chinese%20investments%20in%20the%20future.%20Investments%20from%20China%20have%20had%20to%20face%20government%20scrutiny%20since%20the%20issuance%20of%20Press%20Note%203%20in%20April%202020.%20The%20notification%20was%20seen%20as%20an%20effort%20by%20the%20government%20to%20direct%20Chinese%20capital%20in%20desirable%20domains.%20However%2C%20the%20standoff%20in%20Ladakh%20and%20the%20subsequent%20killing%20of%20Indian%20soldiers%20during%20the%20clashes%20in%20the%20Galwan%20Valley%20in%20June%202020%20extinguished%20any%20appetite%20for%20Chinese%20investments.%20That%20situation%20seems%20to%20be%20changing%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20it%20was%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Ffinance%2Finvestment-proposals-from-border-nations-201-denied-124-approved%2Farticleshow%2F109443275.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2211%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Ffinance%2Finvestment-proposals-from-border-nations-201-denied-124-approved%2Farticleshow%2F109443275.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%C2%A0that%20since%20April%202020%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20has%20approved%20124%20investment%20proposals%20from%20bordering%20countries%20and%20rejected%20201.%20Around%20200%20proposals%20are%20said%20to%20be%20pending%20with%20the%20government.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20these%20proposals%20were%20from%20China.%20While%20the%20scrutiny%20under%20Press%20Note%203%20remains%20active%2C%20there%20has%20been%20some%20easing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20MG%20Motor-JSW%20Deal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20in%20March%2C%20the%20long-discussed%20joint%20venture%20between%20MG%20Motor%20India%20and%20JSW%20Group%20was%20finally%20sealed.%20It%20entailed%20Chinese%20auto%20giant%20SAIC%20Motor%20divesting%20a%2051%25%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20in%20May%2C%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2212%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-may-permit-chinese-electronic-firms-to-invest-on-a-select-basis-124050200186_1.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2213%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-may-permit-chinese-electronic-firms-to-invest-on-a-select-basis-124050200186_1.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%C2%A0emerged%20that%20the%20government%20had%20begun%20moving%20on%20approving%20Chinese%20investment%20proposals%20with%20Indian%20firms%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis.%20In%20July%2C%20it%20was%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookbusiness.com%2Fnews%2Findian-government-to-fast-track-approvals-for-chinese-investments-in-electronics-automobiles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2215%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookbusiness.com%2Fnews%2Findian-government-to-fast-track-approvals-for-chinese-investments-in-electronics-automobiles%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20government%20had%20notified%20electronics%20and%20automobile%20manufacturers%20about%20plans%20to%20establish%20an%20inter-ministerial%20panel%20to%20accelerate%20the%20approval%20process%20for%20investment%20proposals%20from%20Chinese%20firms%20in%20Indian%20companies.%20The%20assessment%20would%20require%20the%20proposals%20to%20meet%20certain%20conditions%2C%20such%20as%20the%20significance%20of%20investment%20and%20technology%20for%20enhancing%20the%20local%20manufacturing%20supply%20chain%2C%20exclusion%20of%20Chinese%20nationals%20from%20the%20management%20and%20board%20of%20the%20investee%20firm%20and%20the%20Indian%20entity%20holding%20a%20majority%20stake%20in%20any%20joint%20venture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2216%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-to-fast-track-china-visas-after-businesses-complain-of-delays-124071700088_1.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2217%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-to-fast-track-china-visas-after-businesses-complain-of-delays-124071700088_1.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%C2%A0indicated%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20was%20looking%20to%20fast-track%20visas%20for%20Chinese%20technicians%20and%20engineers%2C%20given%20that%20delays%20were%20hurting%20Indian%20industry.%20Then%20in%20late%20August%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2218%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Fforeign-trade%2Fforbidden-no-more-india-begins-oking-chinese-proposals%2Farticleshow%2F112691334.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2219%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Fforeign-trade%2Fforbidden-no-more-india-begins-oking-chinese-proposals%2Farticleshow%2F112691334.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20inter-ministerial%20panel%20had%20approved%20five%20to%20six%20investment%20proposals%20involving%20Chinese%20entities%20in%20the%20electronics%20manufacturing%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Good%20Approach%2C%20But%20Not%20Without%20Perils%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20open%20to%20Chinese%20capital%20and%20talent%2C%20particularly%20those%20that%20aid%20the%20development%20of%20India's%20manufacturing%20sector%20and%20deepen%20linkages%20with%20global%20value%20chains%2C%20is%20a%20pragmatic%20and%20prudent%20approach.%20It%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20in%20India's%20larger%20strategic%20interest%20to%20do%20so.%20This%20is%20not%20to%20argue%20that%20there%20isn't%20any%20need%20for%20scrutiny.%20The%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20is%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2220%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2024%2FAug%2F31%2Fjaishankar-says-chinese-investments-should-come-under-thorough-scrutiny-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%3Ca%20data-linkindex%3D%5C%2221%5C%22%20data-auth%3D%5C%22NotApplicable%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2024%2FAug%2F31%2Fjaishankar-says-chinese-investments-should-come-under-thorough-scrutiny-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eright%20to%20argue%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%2C%20as%20he%20did%20at%20a%20public%20forum%20last%20week%2C%20that%20given%20the%20current%20geopolitical%20scenario%20and%20India's%20peculiar%20challenges%20with%20China%2C%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bcommon%20sense%20that%20investments%20from%20China%20should%20be%20scrutinised%26quot%3B.%20However%2C%20this%20should%20not%20be%20an%20ad%20hoc%20process.%20It%20is%20imperative%20to%20establish%20a%20new%20investment%20review%20mechanism%20with%20clear%20guidelines%2C%20conditions%20and%20timelines.%20This%20will%20engender%20greater%20predictability%20for%20industry%2C%20and%20ensure%20adequate%20democratic%20oversight.%20Such%20a%20process%20should%20also%20entail%20delineating%20a%20narrow%20set%20of%20sub-sectors%20as%20critical%20from%20a%20national%20security%20perspective%20and%20therefore%20walled%20off%20from%20Chinese%20entities.%20This%20list%20can%20evolve%20dynamically%20following%20periodic%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20Indian%20industry%2C%20working%20with%20Chinese%20entities%20and%20being%20reliant%20on%20Chinese%20capital%20is%20likely%20to%20always%20remain%20a%20perilous%20endeavour.%20Politics%20and%20security%20have%20always%20come%20first%20in%20the%20India-China%20dynamic.%20Events%20over%20the%20past%20seven%20years%20since%20the%20Doklam%20stand-off%20have%20only%20further%20entrenched%20this%20trend.%20In%20addition%2C%20given%20the%20structural%20fau