med-if-mid-air-rolls-royce-engine-part-failure-poses-wider-risk-13208852%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fairlines-to-be-fully-informed-if-mid-air-rolls-royce-engine-part-failure-poses-wider-risk-13208852%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chinese%20farmers%20across%2014%20towns%20are%20spraying%20industrial%20sulfur%20on%20wolfberries%20so%20they'd%20be%20'red%20and%20beautiful%3A'%20state%20media%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close-up%20shot%20of%20wolfberries%2C%20also%20known%20as%20goji%20berries%2C%20in%20the%20fingers%20of%20a%20human%20hand.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d69bfa14a5cd1fcc8c87d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221837%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWolfberries%20are%20popular%20in%20Chinese%20cuisine%20and%20traditional%20medicine.%3Cp%3ERoberto%20Gonzalez%2FOrlando%20Sentinel%2FTribune%20News%20Service%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWolfberry%20farmers%20in%20China%20were%20caught%20smoking%20their%20crops%20with%20industrial%20sulfur%20to%20preserve%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChinese%20state%20media%20aired%20clips%20of%20workers%20washing%20the%20berries%20in%20thick%2C%20foaming%20chemicals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMerchants%20and%20workers%20told%20the%20broadcaster%20they%20knew%20the%20berries%20were%20unsafe%20but%20that%20they%20looked%20better.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChinese%20state%20broadcaster%20CCTV%20has%20unveiled%20details%20of%20a%20second%20major%20food%20scandal%20to%20rock%20the%20country%20this%20year%2C%20this%20time%20involving%20wolfberries%20smoked%20and%20soaked%20in%20prohibited%20chemicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftv.cctv.com%2F2024%2F09%2F02%2FVIDEdBIwDvj7LcJh8a7eH9Ys240902.shtml%3Fspm%3DC52448022284.P5Ttlwv9L2md.0.0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20aired%20on%20Sunday%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20broadcaster%20spoke%20to%20wolfberry%20farmers%20and%20merchants%20in%20a%20region%20spanning%2014%20towns%20in%20Jingyuan%20County%2C%20Gansu%20province.%20The%20report%20also%20covered%20farms%20in%20Golmud%2C%20a%20city%20in%20Qinghai%20province.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20half%20a%20dozen%20farm%20workers%20and%20dealers%20openly%20described%20on%20camera%20how%20farms%20would%20soak%20the%20berries%20in%20sodium%20metabisulfite%2C%20a%20banned%20substance%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20and%20spray%20them%20with%20industrial%20sulfur%20to%20preserve%20their%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ones%20smoked%20with%20sulfur%20are%20red%20and%20beautiful%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20store%20owner%20told%20the%20broadcaster.%20%26quot%3BWith%20the%20sulfur%2C%20you%20can%20store%20it%20longer%2C%20and%20pests%20don't%20grow.%20Its%20toxicity%20is%20high.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECCTV%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftv.cctv.com%2F2024%2F09%2F02%2FVIDEp9rMWUjeopakjL2wfnG8240902.shtml%3Fspm%3DC52448022284.P5Ttlwv9L2md.0.0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaired%20footage%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20farm%20workers%20preparing%20vats%20of%20thick%2C%20foaming%20sodium%20metabisulfite%20before%20washing%20the%20wolfberries%20in%20the%20hazardous%20chemical.%20Sodium%20metabisulfite%20is%20sometimes%20used%20in%20food%20preservation%20but%20is%20prohibited%20in%20the%20local%20wolfberry%20industry%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chinadaily.com.cn%2Fa%2F202409%2F02%2FWS66d5ae12a3108f29c1fc9ac8.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20state%20media.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20farms%20would%20also%20add%20in%20the%20step%20of%20smoking%20the%20wolfberries%20with%20industrial%20sulfur%20in%20place%20of%20sun-drying%20their%20crop%2C%20according%20to%20clips%20published%20by%20CCTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWolfberries%2C%20also%20known%20as%20goji%20berries%2C%20are%20popular%20in%20Chinese%20traditional%20medicine%20and%20dishes%20such%20as%20hotpot%2C%20and%20were%20marketed%20as%20a%20superfood%20in%20the%20West.%20In%202023%2C%20mainland%20China%20exported%20an%20estimated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.forestry.gov.cn%2Fc%2Fwww%2Flcdt%2F582002.jhtml%23%3A~%3Atext%3D2023%25E5%25B9%25B4%25EF%25BC%258C%25E6%2588%2591%25E5%259B%25BD%25E6%259E%25B8%25E6%259D%259E%25E5%2587%25BA%25E5%258F%25A3%2C%25E5%2585%2583%25EF%25BC%258C%25E5%2590%258C%25E6%25AF%2594%25E5%25A2%259E%25E5%258A%25A023.1%2525%25E3%2580%2582%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E14%2C000%20metric%20tons%20of%20wolfberries.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20like%20you%20who%20sell%20in%20other%20places%20all%20have%20no%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20merchant%20told%20CCTV.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20has%20a%20nice%20appearance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20merchants%20and%20farmers%20spoke%20of%20the%20harms%20of%20consuming%20wolfberries%20tainted%20by%20the%20chemicals%20but%20said%20the%20practice%20was%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20sulfur%2C%20you%20sell%20at%2017%20yuan%20to%2018%20yuan%20per%20catty.%20Without%20smoking%2C%20it's%2010%20yuan%20per%20catty%2C%209%20yuan%20per%20catty.%20That's%20not%20a%20good%20price%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20rural%20farm%20worker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECCTV%20said%20its%20staff%20tested%20the%20wolfberries%20and%20found%20them%20all%20unsafe%20for%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20day%20after%20the%20report%20was%20released%2C%20the%20Jingyuan%20County%20Food%20Safety%20Committee%20office%20announced%20that%20it%20had%20launched%20an%20investigation%20into%20local%20wolfberry%20production%20and%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20responsible%20for%20violations%20of%20the%20law%20and%20regulations%20will%20be%20severely%20punished%20according%20to%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmp.weixin.qq.com%2Fs%2FDvTSegyCLIRguY1UukJSlw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffice%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Golmud%20city%20government%20released%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmp.weixin.qq.com%2Fs%2FQ7_LJW2fn9XOwe2IJ3L7fg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilar%20statement%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wolfberry%20scandal%20comes%20just%20two%20months%20after%20another%20major%20food-related%20safety%20incident%20stunned%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20July%2C%20state%20outlet%20Beijing%20News%20said%20it%20had%20uncovered%20multiple%20instances%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-panics-open-secret-cooking-oil-fuel-chemical-tanks-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunwashed%20chemical%20tankers%20being%20used%20to%20transport%20cooking%20oil%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20practice%20had%20become%20so%20common%20that%20workers%20spoke%20of%20it%20as%20an%20industry%20standard%2C%20per%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20been%20plagued%20for%20decades%20by%20a%20history%20of%20food%20scandals%20%E2%80%94%20from%20contaminated%20milk%20powder%20to%20gutter%20oil%20being%20re-used%20in%20restaurants%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20whittled%20away%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-food-scandal-middle-class-buy-direct-farms-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edomestic%20consumer%20faith%20in%20commercially%20sold%20foods.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20his%20early%20days%20as%20China's%20top%20leader%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%20has%20promised%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20food%20safety%20breaches%2C%20saying%20they%20would%20be%20central%20to%20how%20people%20perceived%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20our%20party%2C%20while%20governing%20China%2C%20cannot%20even%20ensure%20food%20safety%2C%20and%20cannot%20do%20so%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20then%20people%20will%20start%20to%20question%20whether%20we%20are%20qualified%20to%20govern%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllegations%20of%20excessive%20sulfur%20fumigation%20in%20the%20Chine