%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lonely%20Dolphin%20Terrorises%20Japan%20Beach%20Town%20With%20Series%20Of%20Attacks%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20single%20bottlenose%20dolphin%2C%20who%20might%20have%20been%20separated%20from%20its%20pod%2C%20is%20being%20considered%20responsible%20for%20a%20troubling%20series%20of%20attacks%20on%20swimmers%20in%20Tsurga%2C%20a%20seaside%20town%20in%20Fukui%20Prefecture%20in%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20incident%20occurred%20on%20August%2020%2C%20when%20a%20man%20in%20his%2050s%20was%20bitten%20on%20both%20hands%20as%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20drive%20off%20the%20dolphin.%20This%20attack%20marks%20the%2018th%20reported%20case%20since%20July%2021%20and%20the%20second%20within%20a%20span%20of%20two%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NBC%20News%2C%20the%20region%20has%20seen%20over%2048%20dolphin%20bite%20incidents%20in%20the%20last%203%20years%20with%20some%20victims%20suffering%20major%20injuries%20including%20broken%20bones.%20Most%20of%20the%20bites%20however%20were%20minor%20--%20some%20little%20more%20than%20scratches%20--%20but%20in%20one%20recent%20incident%2C%20an%20elementary%20school%20child%20wound%20up%20requiring%2020%20to%2030%20stitches%2C%20coastguard%20official%20Shoichi%20Takeuchi%20told%20AFP.%20The%20recent%20biting%20incident%20required%20beach%20staff%20to%20coax%20a%20dolphin%20away%20from%20a%20swimming%20area%20using%20water%20skis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Coast%20Guard%20notice%20warned%20of%20the%20potential%20dangers%20of%20the%20rising%20number%20of%20dolphin%20bites%2C%20stating%2C%20%26quot%3BLast%20year%2C%20there%20were%20many%20incidents%20in%20which%20swimmers%20were%20bitten%20by%20dolphins%2C%20with%20some%20requiring%20more%20than%2010%20stitches.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20suspect%20a%20lonely%20male%20dolphin%20behind%20these%20attacks%20as%20injuries%20on%20the%20dorsal%20fin%20of%20the%20dolphin%20involved%20in%20the%20last%20incident%20match%20those%20of%20a%20dolphin%20off%20the%20coast%20spotted%20last%20year%2C%20provided%20dorsal%20fins%20are%20unique%20to%20each%20dolphin%2C%20similar%20to%20fingerprints%20in%20the%20case%20of%20human%20beings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETadamichi%20Morisaka%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20Cetacean%20Research%20Center%20at%20Japan's%20Mie%20University%2C%20who%20has%20seen%20photographs%2C%20told%20NHK%2C%20Japan%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20reasonable%20to%20assume%20that%20they're%20the%20same%20individual.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20said%20that%20this%20particular%20dolphin%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20accustomed%20to%20human%20interaction%20over%20the%20years%20leading%20to%20his%20behaviour%20as%20it%20is%20unusual%20for%20bottlenose%20dolphins%20to%20approach%2C%20interact%20or%20bite%20with%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20mail%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%20%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fdolphin-attacks-swimmers-lonely-japan-rcna168349%5C%22%3ENBC%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Morisaka%20also%20said%20the%20dolphin%20mainly%20wants%20to%20merely%20%26quot%3Binteract%20with%20humans%26quot%3B%2C%20possibly%20owing%20to%20its%20loneliness%20rather%20than%20harm%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20executive%20and%20founding%20director%20of%20Dolphin%20Research%20Australia%2C%20Elizabeth%20Hawkins%2C%20further%20said%2C%20that%20the%20animal%20may%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bsociable%20solitary%20dolphin%26quot%3B%20that%20has%20somehow%20got%20isolated.%20And%2C%20when%20socially%20isolated%2C%20Hawkins%20said%2C%20they%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20quite%20pushy%2C%20they%20can%20be%20quite%20aggressive%2C%20they%20can%20bite.%26quot%3B%20Hence%2C%20she%20emphasized%20the%20necessity%20of%20ensuring%20the%20creature%20is%20given%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20situation%20develops%2C%20local%20officials%20continue%20to%20monitor%20the%20dolphin's%20behaviour%20and%20advise%20caution%20for%20those%20entering%20water.%